column12: Did some adjustments that "felt good" with this print after reading several other notices. Turned out quite good.

column13: Haven't done any tests for the resins but happy with the results. Slow lift speed as people say monocure is thick

column12: Could possibly lower the bottom exposure.
Same model as the Elegoo ABS-Like grey I submitted, and same exact settings.  This resin is just a few bucks cheaper so I gave it a shot.
Smaller test print, only 10cm long, used Chitu's auto supports and didn't check them and print was successful.
Makes perfect supports that separate cleanly.
Grey Level: 3, Image Blur: Yes, Image Blur Pixel: 2
A 3 second exposure time is doable if the model is small, otherwise it will fall off the supports
